  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Among the top 200 TGs regulated by STAT1 in classical monocytes, 67 of them overlap with the GWAS genes, which is statistically significant with a P value of less than 0.01 based on a background distribution from a random selection of TFs (one-sided bootstrap hypothesis testing).",
    "The numbers of overlapped TGs are all significant for the top 500, 1,000, 2,000 and 5,000 TGs (Fig. 5d).",
    "Apart from GWAS-relevant genes, we collected the DEGs between inflamed biopsies and non-inflamed biopsies 71 and we found that these DEGs significantly overlapped with the top-ranked TGs of STAT1 (one-sided bootstrap hypothesis testing; Fig. 5e).",
    "The lack of significant overlap between DEGs and GWAS genes (P = 0.15, two-sided Fisher's exact test) but the significant overlap of both DEGs and GWAS with the top-ranked TGs of STAT1 indicates the robustness and unbiased nature of our method.",
    "Finally, we extracted the sub-network of the eight candidate TFs from the classical monocyte trans-regulatory network for IBD (Fig. 5f)."
  ],
